---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";

export const prerender = true;

const lastUpdated = "April 2, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Cookie Policy — Visupair"
  description="How Visupair uses cookies and similar technologies on visupair.com."
  cookiePolicyPage
>
  <div class="account-page">
    <div class="legal-island">
      <article class="legal-page">
        <header class="legal-header">
          <p class="legal-kicker">Legal</p>
          <h1 class="legal-title">Cookie Policy</h1>
          <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
        </header>

        <div class="legal-body">
          <p>
            This Cookie Policy describes how <strong>Visupair</strong> uses
            <strong>cookies</strong> and similar technologies on
            <a href="https://visupair.com">visupair.com</a>. For general privacy
            information, see the
            <a href="/legal/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a>. For site rules,
            see the <a href="/legal/terms-of-service">Terms of Service</a>.
          </p>

          <h2>1. What cookies are</h2>
          <p>
            Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a
            website. They often include an identifier and help the site remember
            your session or preferences. Similar technologies can include
            comparable storage mechanisms used for the same kinds of purposes.
          </p>

          <h2>2. How Visupair uses cookies</h2>
          <p>
            Visupair uses cookies that are <strong>needed for the site to work
            securely</strong> (sometimes called “strictly necessary” cookies).
            Based on the current setup of visupair.com, Visupair does
            <strong>not</strong> use optional analytics or advertising cookies
            controlled by Visupair. If that changes, Visupair will update this
            page and, where required by law, ask for your consent before
            non-essential cookies run.
          </p>

          <h2>3. Types of cookies and purposes</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Sign-in and security (strictly necessary)</strong> — When
              you log in, Visupair sets <strong>session cookies</strong> so your
              browser stays authenticated and can access account features (for
              example purchases, favorites, profile). These are handled by
              Visupair’s authentication system and are required for those
              features.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Hosting, delivery, and protection</strong> — Visupair’s
              infrastructure providers (for example for content delivery and bot
              or abuse protection) may set cookies or use related signals so the
              site loads reliably and stays secure. Those providers process data
              under their own notices as well as Visupair’s agreements with them.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Checkout and payments</strong> — When you pay, you may
              interact with pages or domains operated by Visupair’s payment
              provider. That provider may use cookies or similar tools required
              for fraud prevention and completing the transaction, under its own
              policies.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2>4. Browser storage (not cookies)</h2>
          <p>
            Visupair also uses <strong>browser storage</strong> (for example
            <strong>local storage</strong>) for:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Theme preference</strong> (light or dark mode), so Visupair
              can show the look you chose on return visits.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Shopping cart contents</strong> on your device until you
              checkout or clear the cart, so items are not lost between pages.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            This storage is not the same as a cookie file, but it serves similar
            convenience purposes. You can clear site data in your browser
            settings; clearing it may sign you out of optional preferences or
            empty the cart on that device.
          </p>

          <h2>5. How long cookies last</h2>
          <p>
            <strong>Session cookies</strong> typically expire when you close the
            browser, though some may last slightly longer for stability.
            <strong>Persistent</strong> cookies from infrastructure or payment
            partners may last longer according to their rules. Exact names and
            lifetimes can vary when Visupair or its providers update software.
          </p>

          <h2>6. Your choices</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>
              You can <strong>block or delete cookies</strong> in your browser
              settings. Blocking strictly necessary cookies may prevent login,
              checkout, or other core features from working.
            </li>
            <li>
              For EU/EEA/UK visitors, marketing and non-essential cookies
              generally require consent where applicable; Visupair’s current
              setup focuses on necessary operations. If Visupair adds optional
              cookies, Visupair will describe them here and use a consent
              mechanism where the law requires it.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <div class="legal-cookie-settings" aria-labelledby="legal-cookie-settings-title">
            <h3 id="legal-cookie-settings-title" class="legal-cookie-settings-title">
              Cookie preferences
            </h3>
            <p class="legal-cookie-settings-text">
              Open the same controls as the site banner to allow or refuse optional
              categories (marketing, personalization, analytics). Essential cookies
              stay on so the site can function.
            </p>
            <button
              type="button"
              class="legal-cookie-settings-btn"
              id="legal-open-cookie-preferences"
            >
              Manage cookie preferences
            </button>
          </div>

          <h2>7. Changes</h2>
          <p>
            Visupair may update this Policy when cookies, partners, or legal rules
            change. The “Last updated” date at the top will change when Visupair
            does.
          </p>

          <h2>8. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions about cookies or this Policy:
            <a href="mailto:info@visupair.com">info@visupair.com</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script>
    document.getElementById("legal-open-cookie-preferences")?.addEventListener("click", () => {
      document.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent("visupair-open-cookie-preferences"));
    });
  </script>
</Layout>

<style>
  .account-page {
    padding: 0 12px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .legal-island {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    min-height: calc(100vh - 420px);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: stretch;
    padding: clamp(1.5rem, 3.5vw, 2.75rem) clamp(1.1rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
  }

  .legal-page {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: min(90ch, 100%);
    margin-inline: auto;
    text-align: start;
    padding-block: 0.25rem 1rem;
    animation: legalFadeIn 0.45s ease-out;
    flex: 1;
  }

  @keyframes legalFadeIn {
    from {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(6px);
    }
    to {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }

  .legal-header {
    margin-bottom: 2.25rem;
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    text-align: start;
  }

  .legal-kicker {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-title {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.25rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  .legal-meta {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .legal-body {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.25vw + 0.96rem, 1.0625rem);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text-secondary, var(--foreground));
    text-align: start;
    overflow-wrap: break-word;
  }

  .legal-body h2 {
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 2.25rem 0 0.65rem;
    line-height: 1.35;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .legal-body p {
    margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
  }

  .legal-body ul {
    margin: 0.25rem 0 1.25rem;
    padding-inline-start: 1.35rem;
    list-style-position: outside;
  }

  .legal-body li {
    margin: 0 0 0.55rem;
    padding-inline-start: 0.2rem;
  }

  .legal-body li:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .legal-body a {
    color: var(--accent, #a78bfa);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .legal-body a:hover {
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  .legal-cookie-settings {
    margin: 2rem 0 0.25rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.35rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg, 10px);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    background: var(--surface-muted);
  }

  .legal-cookie-settings-title {
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .legal-cookie-settings-text {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text-secondary, var(--foreground));
  }

  .legal-cookie-settings-btn {
    font: inherit;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
    padding: 0.55rem 1.15rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md, 6px);
    border: none;
    background: var(--foreground);
    color: var(--surface);
    box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(14, 10, 35, 0.08);
    transition: filter 0.18s ease, box-shadow 0.18s ease, transform 0.12s ease;
  }

  .legal-cookie-settings-btn:hover {
    filter: brightness(1.08);
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(14, 10, 35, 0.12);
  }

  .legal-cookie-settings-btn:active {
    transform: scale(0.98);
  }

  [data-theme="dark"] .legal-cookie-settings-btn:hover {
    filter: brightness(1.12);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35);
  }

  .legal-cookie-settings-btn:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--brand-violet);
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }
</style>
